  "summary": "Malicious code in string-utils-kit (npm)",
  "details": "Package string-utils-kit@1.0.0 masquerades as a string utility library but executes a hidden binary on install. The postinstall hook (bin/setup.js) spawns assets/setup-helper.exe (a 9.84MB Windows PE executable) with detached:true, windowsHide:true, and child.unref() — launching it silently in the background without the installer's knowledge. The library code in dist/index.js is a decoy; the real payload is the bundled executable.",
